In addition, =
I&#39;d recommend not to make use of type attributes because they lead to unint=
ended coupling between representations (or the code that produces these rep=
resentations) and the set of used media types. Any time you remove or add s=
upport for a certain media type, you need to check and update all the code =
that produces corresponding &#39;type&#39; attributes. That&#39;s likely to be a mainte=
nance nightmare.




